programme.title: Focus
programme.desc: Nicky has studied the science of human nature his whole life, and understands precisely how to earn anyone's trust, or fool them into never noticing he's stealing their watch, or wallet, or anything they might have that Nicky can sell. In the movie's opening sequence, he's eating at a New York restaurant when the gorgeous Jess approaches his table and asks him to pretend to be her boyfriend so that she can avoid a particularly determined guy at the bar who won't stop hitting on her. The two of them hit it off, but he quickly figures out that she's running a scam on him and soon turns the tables on her and her partner. Undaunted, Jess begs Nicky to teach her what he knows about the criminal life, and he brings her in on a plan to steal from as many people as possible during Super Bowl week in New Orleans. She turns out to be a natural, and quickly learns the ropes of this unscrupulous world. Nicky and Jess seem to be falling for each other, but Nicky's actions at the end of their New Orleans trip force Jess to reassess their relationship. Three years later, Nicky enters into a deal with Garriga (Rodrigo Santoro), a wealthy playboy who has a software program that will help his Formula 1 team triumph. Nicky agrees to help Garriga sell a fake version of the program to his competitors, but as the plan goes into motion he discovers Jess and Garriga are a couple. As old feelings complicate the new arrangement, Nicky must also contend with the no-nonsense Owens (Gerald McRaney), Garriga's head-of-security who openly distrusts Nicky(n)

programme.title: Snow Angels
programme.desc: Director/screenwriter David Gordon Green adapts Stewart O'Nan's popular novel to the screen in this feature, which tells the parallel tales of a teenager named Arthur (Michael Angarano) and his onetime babysitter Annie (Kate Beckinsale) -- whose turbulent relationship with her estranged husband, Glenn (Sam Rockwell), leads the small-town waitress down a troubled path. Arthur is a high-school student from a dysfunctional family, and does everything in his power to avoid hanging around the house while mom and dad quarrel. When he's not practicing his trombone and performing with the high-school marching band, Arthur can usually be found bussing tables at the local Chinese restaurant and flirting with older waitress Annie. Annie used to be Arthur's babysitter, and is currently struggling to separate from her former high-school sweetheart, Glenn. But being a single mother isn't easy, especially since the troubled Glenn wants nothing more than to clean up his act and reunite his family. Back at school, Arthur and pretty classmate Lila (Olivia Thirlby) have been bonding over their mutual love for all things geeky. Though the casual friendship shows promise of evolving into something more when Lila expresses her true feelings for Arthur, he can't help but becoming distracted by his chaotic family life: his father is moving out of the family home, and his mother is doing everything in her power to maintain some semblance of normalcy. Realizing that happiness is fleeting as his family becomes shattered and Annie experiences a series of distressing encounters with Glenn, Arthur gradually begins to fall for Lisa despite his growing cynicism concerning long-term relationships. Later, on a cold winter morning, Glenn and Annie's past catches up with them in a blinding flash, and the lives of everyone they know are suddenly and irrevocably changed(n)

programme.title: Bend It like Beckham
programme.desc: An independent-minded young woman discovers the joys of football, much to her family's chagrin, in this upbeat British comedy drama. Jess Bhamra (Parminder Nagra) is an 18-year-old growing up in West London, where her family has taken every effort to stay in touch with its Indian heritage. Jess' father and mother (Anupam Kher and Shaheen Khan) are after their daughter to go to law school, learn to cook a traditional Indian dinner, and settle down with a nice Indian boy -- the latter of which is high on the agenda of her older sister Pinky (Archie Panjabi), who is soon to wed her longtime beau Teetu (Kulvinder Ghir). However, her family is unaware that Jess has a secret passion -- football (or soccer, as it's known in North America). While Jess' enthusiasm for football star David Beckham is obvious, given the fact his photos cover the walls of her room, her parents don't know that in her spare time she likes to play a friendly game in the park with some of the boys in the neighborhood. One day, while Jess and her pals kick the ball around, she meets Jules (Keira Knightley), who is quite impressed with Jess' skills. Jules plays with a local semi-pro women's football team, the Hounslow Harriers, and she thinks Jess has what it takes to make the team. Jess knows that her parents would never approve of their daughter playing football, so she doesn't tell them, and starts spinning an increasingly complex series of lies as she tries to keep up a double life as a student and a footballer. Jess soon discovers a number of her new friends have their own problems to overcome; Jules dreams of playing pro ball in America, but has to deal with her stubborn and disapproving mother (Juliet Stevenson), while Joe (Jonathan Rhys Meyers), Hounslow's Irish coach, still struggles with the disappointment of a career as a professional athlete which was dashed by a knee injury. Bend It Like Beckham was a significant box-office success in Great Britain and Europe, but didn't reach American theaters until nearly a year after it debuted in the U.K(n)

programme.desc: Although the once-hot game show Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? had lost its luster as a prime-time ABC offering, the producers felt that there was enough life left in the property to warrant a Monday-through-Friday syndicated version. Taking over from the earlier series' host Regis Philbin was Meredith Vieira of The View. To make certain that the series would not be bankrupted after its first week on the air, the questions posed to contestants were considerably harder than those on the prime-time incarnation. Also, the famous "fastest finger" round was eliminated, taking some of the pressure off the contestants when they struggled to come up with answers. The most noteworthy change from the original version was the absence of Regis Philbin's familiar catchphrases: One would never hear Meredith Vieira chime in with the legendary "Is that your final answer?" The syndicated Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? was launched on September 16, 2002(n)

programme.title: Peacock
programme.desc: A Nebraska bank clerk finds his tenuous grip on reality slipping after a freak train accident reveals his deepest secret to the entire community. John Skillpa (Cillian Murphy) is a reserved bank teller living in the tight-knit community of Peacock. He may live by himself, but he's never alone; John has two personalities. His alter ego is Emma, but Emma has always been a well-kept secret -- until now. When a passing caboose jumps the rails and comes slamming through John's backyard, the neighbors all race to his aid and are surprised to find Emma wandering about dazed and confused. Instinctively assuming Emma to be John's wife, they rally around the Skillpas in support. But the harder they try to get closer to Emma, the deeper John slips into psychosis. The key to his mystery-shrouded past resting in the hands of young, overburdened mother Maggie (Ellen Page), John finds his two personalities clashing as his fragile deception becomes ever more difficult to maintain. Susan Sarandon, Keith Carradine, Bill Pullman, and Josh Lucas co-star(n)

programme.title: Rooster Cogburn
programme.desc: (1975) John Wayne reprises his role as Federal Marshal "Rooster" Cogburn, for which he won his sole Oscar in True Grit , six years earlier. This time out, the rambunctious, one-eyed lawman finds himself in pursuit of a gang of outlaws who've made off with a consignment of nitro-glycerine. As they flee, the violent criminals stumble across a village in Indian Territory, where they rape the women and murder most of the inhabitants. Bible-bashing spinster Eula Goodnight (Katharine Hepburn) survives the massacre and insists on Cogburn taking her along to avenge her father's killing. Despite the grim start to the adventure, Stuart Miller's light-hearted Western is shot through with humour and is especially noted for the sparky exchanges between the two lead stars. Premiere(n)

programme.title: License to Drive
programme.desc: Les (Corey Haim) is embarrassed when he fails his driving test in this routine teen comedy. His buddies are depending on him to provide the wheels for the weekend, but Les is more interested in his Saturday date with Mercedes (Heather Graham). Les secretly steals his grandfather's immaculate 1972 Cadillac for the adventure. The dream date soon turns into a nightmare when Dean (Corey Feldman) bothers Les with camera flashes and cigar smoke, and his sloppy-drunk date dances on the hood of the car with high heels. The car is towed when he parks illegally, and later the teens are chased by revved-up motorheads who challenge him to a race. Carol Kane and Richard Masur play Les' parents(n)

programme.title: Soul Plane
programme.desc: After a humiliating experience on an airplane, Nashawn Wade sues the airline and is awarded a huge settlement. Determined to make good with the money, Nashawn creates the full service airline of his dreams, complete with sexy stewardesses, funky music, a hot onboard dance club, and a bathroom attendant(n)

programme.title: Men in Black II
programme.desc: Donning dark suits and shades, Tommy Lee Jones and Will Smith return as alien-hunting überagents in this sequel to the 1997 smash hit. This time, the agents are on the trail of a sexy extraterrestrial (Lara Flynn Boyle) determined to destroy the world. Rip Torn, Tony Shalhoub, Johnny Knoxville, Rosario Dawson(n)

programme.title: Evan Almighty
programme.desc: God appears before a sceptical congressman to tell him that his destiny is to be the modern-day Noah and build an ark capable of withstanding a mighty flood. While he initially struggles to come to terms with his task and begins to question his own sanity, the congressman soon finds himself gathering animals, chopping wood and trying to convince his disbelieving family(n)
Jackie Robinson becomes the first coloured American to make it to the Major League Baseball and breaks the colour barrier by signing up with Brooklyn Dodgers(n)

programme.title: Ali
programme.desc: An Oscar-nominated Will Smith stars as Muhammad Ali in Michael Mann's heavyweight biopic of the boxing icon. Co-starring Jamie Foxx and Jon Voight(n)

programme.title: Kiss the Girls
programme.desc: Disturbing thriller about the hunt for a killer - known only as Casanova - who has kidnapped a number of women and murdered two of them. When a detective's niece goes missing, he is drawn into a complex and highly personal investigation. The local police are unappreciative of his efforts, but his niece manages to escape with valuable information about the killer(n)

programme.title: Hitman: Agent 47
programme.desc: Agent 47 (Rupert Friend), known only by the barcode tattoo on his neck, is an elite international assassin. Engineered to be an unstoppable killing machine, 47 is contracted by a covert organization to assassinate high-profile targets on a global scale. He's given the assignment to kill the leader of a crime syndicate who wishes to unlock the secrets behind 47's powers and harness that information into an army of highly skilled hit men. As 47 races to complete his mission, new information emerges about his origins and sparks a race against time as the agent is hunted for the secrets behind his skills. Aleksander Bach directs this reboot of the 2007 action thriller Hitman(n)

programme.title: Suicide Kings
programme.desc: A group of youngsters kidnap a respected Mafia figure(n)

programme.title: Phone Booth
programme.desc: Irishman Colin Farrell plays an egotistical, Bronx-born publicist who's held hostage in a public telephone booth at a busy New York City intersection. His captor: a menacing, self-righteous sniper (Kiefer Sutherland). This taut and entertaining thriller is a briskly paced morality play from director Joel Schumacher. Forest Whitaker, Katie Holmes, Radha Mitchell(n)

programme.title: Crimson Tide
programme.desc: A radical group has seized control of a nuclear missile base and the USS Alabama, a state-of-the-art nuclear submarine, has been ordered into action in this taut thriller. But when a fragmented message arrives onboard to launch a defensive strike against the enemy, suddenly a fiery battle of wills erupts between the veteran sub commander - who never questions orders - and his more cautious second officer, who can't help but suspect a command to start a nuclear war. Gene Hackman and Denzel Washington star(n)

programme.title: Perkins' 14
programme.desc: Dark Ride director Craig Singer returns to the helm with this shocking horror film about a delusional psychopath who creates a unified team of 14 maniacal killers. Produced entirely over the Internet, where writers uploaded story details and actors submitted audition tapes, Perkins' 14 was released into theaters as part of the third After Dark Horror Fest. Ronald Perkins was just six years old when his parents were brutally slaughtered right before his eyes. Unable to overcome the incredible trauma of witnessing such a diabolical event, Perkins becomes convinced that the killers who murdered his parents will eventually return to finish the job they started years ago -- and he plans to be fully prepared to fight back when they do. Years later, when Perkins turns 34, he kidnaps 14 people from his hometown of Stone Cove and sets about reprogramming them to become relentless killing machines. Now, if the killers ever do return, they'll have to get through Perkins' 14 in order to reach their intended target. Trouble is, now that Perkins' 14 are ready for battle, they've become increasingly difficult to contain(n)

programme.title: Dance of the Dead
programme.desc: As prom gets underway and the dead come out to play, the only hope for saving the day is the mismatched couple that can't seem to agree on anything. As the Cosa High School Senior Prom draws near, the local teens are more preoccupied with getting laid and looking good on the big night. But while local teen Jimmy (Jared Kusnitz) seems completely unfazed by all the infectious enthusiasm that's spreading through the student body, his girlfriend Lindsey (Greyson Chadwick) has thrown herself into the teenage ritual and remains determined to have the perfect romantic evening. But it's kind of difficult to enjoy an intimate dance when your classmates are trying to eat your brains, and when the tux-clad teens begin turning blue and munching on flesh, Jimmy and Lindsey are forced to put their differences aside long enough to extinguish the zombie plague before it spreads beyond campus grounds(n)

programme.title: Route 666
programme.desc: The brutal murder of a prison chain gang reverberates through time, leaving an unsuspecting pair of special agents doing battle against the forces of the undead in this tale of highway horror from director William Wesley. When a pair of mafia hitmen force special agents Jack (Lou Diamond Phillips) and Stephanie (Lori Petty) off the beaten path and down a haunted desert shortcut, vengeful ghosts quickly take precedence over begrudged gangsters. Now left to do battle with the forces of evil on a lonely stretch of highway, Jack and Stephanie must face off against the brutal specters or risk losing their lives as well as their souls(n)

programme.title: On Deadly Ground
programme.desc: Action-packed thriller about an oil rig firefighter who opposes an ecologically unsound scheme proposed by his sometime employer. When he learns that the unscrupulous president of Aegis Oil intends to commence drilling on native Inuit land in Alaska, the coolly efficient trouble-shooter joins forces with local people to block the plans(n)

programme.title: Batman: Year One
programme.desc: In this thrilling origin story, Batman (voice of Ben McKenzie) begins his war on crime in Gotham City and decides to join forces with Lt. James Gordon (voice of Bryan Cranston), an honest cop dealing with a corrupt police force. Adapted from the comic-book series by Frank Miller and David Mazzucchelli(n)

programme.title: Be Kind Rewind
programme.desc: Jack Black and Mos Def re-enact everything from Ghostbusters to Rush Hour when the tapes in their video store are wiped. Hit slacker comedy from director Michel Gondry. (2008)(97 mins)(n)

programme.title: The Simpsons Movie
programme.desc: Riotous big-screen animated adventures of the cartoon characters from the TV series. Homer triggers an environmental calamity in Springfield that has far-reaching effects for the town and the planet(n)

programme.title: Blood Diamond
programme.desc: In the role that gave him his third Academy Award nomination, Leonardo DiCaprio stars Blood Diamond as a mercenary who wishes to transform his life by finding a rare pink diamond. In his quest, he is joined by Solomon Vandy, a man who was taken from his family, forced to work in the diamond fields. Sharing completely different life stories but united for the same purpose, both men embark on a trek through rebel territory, in a journey that could save Solomon's family and give Archer a second chance. Jennifer Connelly plays an American journalist whose idealism is tempered by a deepening connection with Archer(n)

programme.title: San Andreas
programme.desc: A helicopter pilot races to rescue his daughter and estranged wife as a series of massive earthquakes devastate California. Meanwhile, a Cal Tech professor attempts to warn other citizens(n)

programme.title: Victor Frankenstein
programme.desc: This fascinating reimagining of the Frankenstein mythos focuses on Igor, the assistant of Victor Frankenstein. When the scientist builds an undead creature that turns dangerous, it's up to Igor to save Frankenstein from both the monster and himself(n)

programme.title: Resident Evil
programme.desc: Alice leads a team of commandos into the multi-national Umbrella Corporation's locked-down bunker, which is controlled by the main computer, The Red Queen. The unit is sealed because of a virus that gassed all the staff but, as Alice and her team discover, the virus has re-animated them. Now, as well as facing the computer's weaponry, they must tackle the living dead to prevent the virus escaping into the outside world. Paul W Anderson's horror thriller is based on the successful computer game(n)

programme.title: Krampus

Liverpool are also tipped by many for honours this year, and have proven themselves to be a potent attacking force under Jurgen Klopp, but it remained to be seen whether they could penetrate a West Brom defence organised by Tony Pulis with as much ease as some of the others they have faced.(n)

programme.title: The Andrew Marr Show
programme.desc: Round-up of the week's stories, featuring interviews with key figures in politics and current affairs, and leafing through the Sunday papers. Including news and weather at 9.00.(n)

programme.title: Sunday Morning Live
programme.desc: Naga Munchetty presents a debate on whether it is racist to want tougher checks on migrants and singer Donny Osmond talks about the ups and downs of stardom and being a Mormon.(n)

programme.title: Sunday Politics London
programme.desc: The week's events at Westminster, presented by Andrew Neil. Including news and a regional round-up.(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Two policemen and a couple of self-confessed `glamorous grannies' are expertly assisted by Catherine Southon and Thomas Plant as they search for bargains in the antiques centres of Lewes, East Sussex. Presenter Tim Wonnacott visits an 18th-century watermill with an intriguing history.(n)

programme.title: Homes Under the Hammer
programme.desc: Developers Lucy Alexander and Martin Roberts explore a terraced property in Kent, a one-bedroom house in Carlisle, and a fire-damaged property in Derby, which are all about to be sold at auction. After the sale, they talk to the new owners about their plans for the houses, and check on their progress at a later date.(n)

programme.title: Escape to the Country
programme.desc: Sonali Shah searches for a property in Hampshire on a budget of £850,000 for a couple hoping to escape their hectic lifestyle. Meanwhile, away from the house-hunt, the presenter meets some of the county's most popular locals.(n)

programme.title: Points of View
programme.desc: Jeremy Vine presents a selection of viewers' comments on BBC shows, a chance to see memorable clips, and an insight into what goes on behind the scenes of new programmes.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Only four bakers remain as the semi-final arrives. This week, the contestants must demonstrate their mastery of patisserie in three more challenges. However, the stakes have never been higher, and a disaster in any one of the rounds might mean the difference between claiming a place in the final, or bowing out early. In the Signature, the bakers must achieve perfect lamination on French pastries, and in the Technical, Paul Hollywood puts the amateurs through their paces with a yeast-based cake with a fruity top and delicate chocolate work. For the Showstopper finale, the competitors face a multiple mini-cake bake, with Paul and fellow judge Mary Berry expecting a high-end finish that demonstrates the bakers' ability to manage their time.(n)

programme.title: Songs of Praise
programme.desc: Aled Jones presents an episode marking the 50th anniversary of the Aberfan disaster, and talks to two survivors of the tragedy about their experience.(n)

programme.title: Attenborough & the Giant Dinosaur
programme.desc: The story of how more than 220 dinosaur bones were found in the Argentinean desert, which were found to have come from a previously undiscovered species, which is the largest land dwelling animal known to have existed. David Attenborough visits the archaeological dig and a laboratory where the remains are being cleaned and analysed with lead scientist Dr Diego Pol and evolutionary biologist Ben Garrod, and meets animators, model-makers, paleontologists and anatomy experts who are working to reconstruct what the 37 metre-long creature would have looked like.(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Anita Rani visits a commercial walnut harvest in Somerset, while Matt Baker meets a man in East Sussex who spent six months living off grid in a tree house made of recycled wood. A botanist reveals how he uses time-lapse filming to record fungi growing, Naomi Wilkinson discovers how conkers became a valuable resource during the First World War, and chef Cyrus Todiwala prepares Indian style sausages using rare breed woodland pork. Including weather for the week ahead.(n)

programme.title: Strictly Come Dancing
programme.desc: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman present the results of last night's contest. The two lowest scoring couples compete in a dance-off, before judges Len Goodman, Darcey Bussell, Bruno Tonioli and Craig Revel Horwood decide who will not be returning for next week's Halloween special. LeAnn Rimes is this week's guest singer.(n)

programme.title: Antiques Roadshow
programme.desc: Fiona Bruce and the team value more rarities at Baddesley Clinton, near Solihull, including a painting entitled The Nudist Colony's Annual Dinner Dance and a silver box which is exceptionally rare but which had a lucky escape from being seriously damaged. Two gold boxes used by 19th-century surgeons to apply snuff provoke a surprised reaction from the crowd.(n)

programme.title: Poldark
programme.desc: Ross and Dwight face trial after the disastrous smuggling incident, while Wheal Grace is faced with closure. Dwight reveals that he will not be marrying Caroline, and is considering joining the navy. George continues to pile pressure on Elizabeth, sending men to pose as tin prospectors, then offers to give her the help she needs if she agrees to marry him. Ross learns that she has accepted the proposal following a mine collapse, and despite Demelza's efforts to stop him, he rides through the night to find her.(n)

programme.title: Match of the Day 2
programme.desc: Mark Chapman presents the day's Premier League highlights, including Chelsea v Manchester United at Stamford Bridge, as Jose Mourinho returned to the club where he won three league titles. Plus, action from Manchester City v Southampton at the Etihad Stadium, and another chance to see Saturday's goals.(n)

programme.title: Tulisa: The Price of Fame
programme.desc: Documentary following the highs and lows of the past 12 months of singer Tulisa Contostavlos' life, including her arrest, charge and suicide attempt. Self-shot diary footage offers an insight into what it is like to be on the receiving end of a tabloid sting, revealing the nature of celebrity culture and how major stars cope with stress. Previously shown on BBC Three.(n)

programme.title: Flight for Freedom
programme.desc: A female pilot in the 1930s strives to overturn prejudices against women in the aviation establishment by carrying out a series of record-breaking flights. Her talents attract the attention of the US government, who enlist her help in carrying out a dangerous secret mission. Drama, starring Rosalind Russell and Fred MacMurray.(n)

programme.title: Wonder Man
programme.desc: Nightclub entertainer Buzzy Bellew witnesses a murder committed by gangster Ten Grand Jackson and is killed by two of his thugs. Buzzy comes back as a ghost and tries to persuade his bookish twin Edwin Dingle to avenge his death by helping the police catch Jackson. Comedy musical, starring Danny Kaye, Virginia Mayo, Vera-Ellen, Donald Woods and Steve Cochran.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.sub-title: Natural World: Heligan - Secrets of the Lost Garden.
programme.desc: The secret lives of the wildlife in the popular Cornish tourist attraction, set against the background of the gardening year. Charlie Hamilton James shoots footage highlighting a variety of creatures inhabiting the estate, including foxes at play in the pleasure gardens after the visitors have left, toads mating and the badgers that enter the tea rooms at night. Narrated by Philippa Forrester.(n)

programme.title: Lost Land of the Jaguar
programme.desc: Steve Backshall reaches the summit of a table-top mountain, after climbing a vertical cliff face nearly as high as the Empire State Building. Meanwhile, Dr George McGavin and Gordon Buchanan have to haul three boats and all their kit through the jungle after finding the rapids of the Rewa River impassable. At the end of the journey, George presents a report on the expedition to the President of Guyana, Bharrat Jagdeo. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Antiques Road Trip
programme.desc: Experts Anita Manning and David Harper embark on the last leg of their journey, travelling from Ayrshire to the Isle of Bute, Glasgow, Renfrewshire and ending at an auction in Paisley. They both take risks in a bid to win the week, but it remains to be seen who will come out on top.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The first of the Northern Ireland heats sees returning contender Chris McGowan and newcomers Mark Abbott and Eddie Attwell prepare their starters for the banquet. There are some varied and exciting dishes as the chefs get creative with pig's heads and potatoes, as well as a reinvention of the classic ploughman's, while there is real shock and emotion when the veteran judge delivers his scores.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The Northern Ireland chefs attempt to impress the judges with their fish courses. Mark Abbott is pushing himself again, plating up a complex fish course of the very finest produce - but at the last minute forgets a key element. Returning chef Chris McGowan refines cod and chips, while Eddie Attwell is getting classical with the king of the sea turbot. The repartee is relentless as the chefs jostle for top place on the leader board and once again there is plenty of emotion as veteran chef Michael O'Hare delivers the scores.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The chefs from the Northern Ireland category turn their attention to main courses, as returning contestant Chris McGowan sets himself the challenge of making his own venison sausages to serve with a venison rack. Eddie Attwell also opts for venison, serving it with a traditional Northern Ireland dish called Dock pudding. Finally, Mark Abbott once again decides to push himself to the limit with a wagyu beef dish served with tongue and corn.(n)

programme.title: Talking Pictures
programme.desc: A look at the TV appearances made over the years by Swedish Academy Award-winning actress Ingrid Bergman, exploring the milestones of her life and career, including her appearances in Casablanca and Spellbound. Narrated by Sylvia Syms.(n)

programme.title: Notorious
programme.desc: An undercover agent falls for the socialite daughter of a convicted German spy and persuades her to feed him information about the activities of a group of Nazi collaborators in Brazil - a dangerous decision that threatens to cost the girl her life as the leader of the gang draws closer to uncovering her secret. Alfred Hitchcock's thriller, starring Cary Grant, Ingrid Bergman, Claude Rains and Louis Calhern.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Members of the public gather at the Imperial War Museum Duxford in Cambridgeshire to present their antiques to James Lewis and Christina Trevanion. Presented by Paul Martin.(n)

programme.title: Nature's Weirdest Events
programme.desc: Chris Packham presents more mysteries and strange stories, including the strange balls of worms that turned up on a road, fish stuck in fences in Texas and how an Australian town became plagued by giant bats. Plus, why so many sperm whales became stranded around the North Sea in 2015, how a robot could help save the Great Barrier Reef and how a spider in the Sahara could help take humans to other planets.(n)

programme.title: Gardeners' World
programme.desc: At Longmeadow, Monty Don gives advice on the plants that need winter protection and thinks ahead to colourful spring bouquets by planting bulbs in the cutting garden. Carol Klein heads to Worcestershire in search of some autumn colour, in a garden designed to reach its peak of flowering in October. Frances Tophill finds out whether there is a north-south divide in the yield and taste of vegetables grown at RHS Rosemoor in Devon and RHS Harlow Carr in Yorkshire, while Zephaniah Lindo investigates the relationship between roots and microscopic fungi.(n)

programme.title: Iolo's Great Welsh Parks
programme.desc: Naturalist Iolo Williams explores historic estates and parklands, examining their role in protecting wildlife and meeting those with inside knowledge. He uses his expertise to locate nocturnal creatures in areas which are open to public access but where natural activity often goes unnoticed.(n)

programme.title: Inside the Commons
programme.desc: Michael Cockerell witnesses battles breaking out over the future of the House as Speaker John Bercow runs into trouble with his own plans for reforming it, while Tory backbencher Zac Goldsmith tries to get voters the power to sack their MPs. Plus, an insight into the challenges of carrying out a multi-billion-pound programme of restoration work while Parliament is sitting, and the events and banqueting team tries to raise money for the upkeep of the palace by hosting fashion shows and film premieres inside the House. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off: An Extra Slice
programme.desc: Reigning Bake Off champion Nadiya Hussain and Scottish Conservative Party leader Ruth Davidson are among those joining host Jo Brand to discuss the semi-final stage of the contest. Plus, unseen footage from the programme and an interview with the contestant who was evicted from the tent on Wednesday.(n)

programme.title: Dad's Army
programme.desc: Captain Mainwaring and his platoon plan to stage a re-enactment of the St George and the dragon story as part of the Wings for Victory fundraising campaign, but discover Hodges and his fellow ARP wardens have had the same idea. Vintage comedy first shown in 1977, starring Arthur Lowe.(n)

programme.title: The School That Got Teens Reading
programme.desc: Documentary charting one Lancashire school's efforts to inspire reluctant teenagers to take up reading for pleasure. Despite receiving otherwise outstanding Ofsted reports, Ripley Academy in Lancaster has been struggling to engage its pupils in one of the most important academic skills. Having exhausted every other technique across hundreds of books, the staff turn to comedian Javone Prince and Blue Peter's Helen Skelton for help in convincing their most reluctant readers to take the plunge.(n)

programme.title: The Invisible Woman
programme.desc: Premiere. A Victorian teacher recalls her former life as an actress, and her relationship with Charles Dickens. She quickly becomes his lover and the inspiration for his work, but the strain of keeping their affair a secret takes its toll on her. Fact-based period drama, directed by and starring Ralph Fiennes, with Felicity Jones and Kristin Scott Thomas.(n)

programme.title: Artsnight
programme.desc: Author and comedian David Baddiel introduces this year's Man Booker Prize shortlist, which provides readers with a view on the very best recent works of fiction available in the English-speaking world. Himself a former Booker Prize judge, Baddiel names the six novels chosen by this year's panel, which consists of Jon Day, Abdulrazak Gurnah, David Harsent and Olivia Williams, and is chaired by Amanda Foreman. Plus, reviewers including Mariella Frostrup, Val McDermid and George `the Poet' Mpanga meet some of the nominated authors, and take a look at the stories and themes covered in the shortlisted entries.(n)

programme.title: Revolutionary Road
programme.desc: Married couple Frank and April Wheeler live a picture-perfect life on the surface, but in truth are growing frustrated with their lot and feel stifled by their situation. When April suggests the family moves to France to start a new life, Frank is persuaded it is a good idea, though when he is offered a stable job with a lucrative pay packet he changes his mind, leaving April a desperate figure longing for an escape. Sam Mendes' 1950s-set drama, starring Kate Winslet, Leonardo DiCaprio, Michael Shannon and Kathy Bates.(n)

programme.title: Andrew Marr's Great Scots: The Writers Who Shaped a Nation
programme.desc: The life of Walter Scott, the prolific novelist and poet who wrote swashbuckling tales of romance and derring-do. However, Andrew Marr reveals his lesser-known side as a political fixer who believed in a proud Scotland inside the UK. Scott brought George IV to his home country and, swathing him in tartan, created an enduring myth of Scotland as a place of romance populated by a brave race doing brave deeds, all clad in kilts.(n)

programme.title: Renoir
programme.desc: The elderly impressionist painter finds fresh inspiration for his work in the form of a young model while living in the Cote d'Azur during 1915. His son Jean returns home injured from the First World War and falls in love with the artist's muse - a relationship that sparks the younger man's rise to become a film-maker. Drama, starring Michel Bouquet, Christa Theret and Vincent Rottiers. In French and Italian.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: The A to Z of TV Gardening
programme.desc: Carol Kirkwood looks at subjects beginning with the letter K, continuing her alphabetical journey through the world of horticulture. Along the way, she gets inspiration and advice from some of the BBC's most popular gardening presenters.(n)

programme.title: Glorious Gardens from Above
programme.desc: Horticulturist Christine Walkden takes to the skies above Cumbria, visiting Levens Hall where she lends a hand planting spring bulbs, and hears some personal memories of a Lakeland lad. She then travels to Holehird to meet the volunteers who have restored a 19th-century garden to its former glory, before discovering the spur of Beatrix Potter's writing career.(n)

programme.title: Gardeners' World
programme.desc: At Longmeadow, Monty Don gives advice on the plants that need winter protection and thinks ahead to colourful spring bouquets by planting bulbs in the cutting garden. Carol Klein heads to Worcestershire in search of some autumn colour, in a garden designed to reach its peak of flowering in October. Frances Tophill finds out whether there is a north-south divide in the yield and taste of vegetables grown at RHS Rosemoor in Devon and RHS Harlow Carr in Yorkshire, while Zephaniah Lindo investigates the relationship between roots and microscopic fungi.(n)

programme.title: Countryfile
programme.desc: Matt Baker and Anita Rani explore the Isle of Wight, where Matt abseils down the walls of Carisbrooke Castle to clear the ivy and works with two donkeys to draw water from a well, while Anita helps local volunteers to round up feral goats and visits a vineyard. Naomi Wilkinson drops in at Ventor Botanic Gardens, Adam Henson meets a commercial deer breeder, and Tom Heap reports on plans to crack down on keeping chickens in cages.(n)

programme.title: The Beechgrove Garden
programme.desc: Jim McColl makes the most of the falling leaves, vacuuming them up to make a mould - which also gives him a chance to demonstrate his new hot-box composter. He also marks the 10th anniversary of Trellis, designed to support therapeutic gardening, as he visits a restorative garden in Banchory-Devenick. Carole Baxter makes her last visit to budget gardener Mieke and her family in Aberdeenshire, showing how to make economical but pretty paths.(n)

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen Best Bites
programme.desc: John Torode presents highlights from throughout the series, offering viewers a chance to revisit some of their favourite moments from previous years in the kitchen.(n)

programme.title: Food & Drink
programme.desc: Michel Roux Jr and resident drinks expert Kate Goodman are joined by leading chef Angela Hartnett as they create ragu and pasta. Journalist Matthew Fort talks about his experiences of eating disappointing, inauthentic Italian dishes, and gastronome Antonio Carluccio celebrates the qualities of the genuine article.(n)

programme.title: MOTD2 Extra
programme.desc: Mark Chapman and guests focus on the headlines from yesterday's matches, as well as news ahead of today's fixtures, which include Chelsea v Manchester United.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Northern Ireland hopefuls Chris McGowan, Mark Abbott and Eddie Attwell serve up their desserts in a last bid to make it through to the regional final. One of the chefs is hoping to beat his boss - a veteran of Great British Menu - by achieving more points than anyone has in the history of the competition. But the kitchen is hot and the chefs are working with chocolate and sugar, and before long disaster strikes.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The two highest-scoring chefs from Northern Ireland cook for judges Oliver Peyton, Prue Leith and Matthew Fort, who are joined by restaurant critic and Editor-at-Large of the Independent Amol Rajan as guest judge. Only one contender can be chosen to represent the region in the national finals, taking them a step closer to cooking at the banquet at the Palace of Westminster.(n)

programme.title: NFL Live
programme.sub-title: American Football: NFL Live: Los Angeles Rams v New York Giants.
programme.desc: Los Angeles Rams v New York Giants (Kick-off 2.30pm). Coverage of the week seven match from Twickenham, where the NFC West and East teams face each other. This is the second of three games to take place in London this season, and the first to be staged at the home of English rugby union, which will host between three and five contests over the next three years. The Giants return to the English capital for the first time since 2007, when they defeated the Miami Dolphins 13-10 in the first regular-season game to be held at Wembley Stadium, while the Rams will hope for a better performance than when they were trounced 45-7 by the New England Patriots in 2012, before they relocated from St Louis. Presented by Nat Coombs, with analysis from Osi Umenyiora and Mike Carlson.(n)

programme.title: Who's Spending Britain's Billions
programme.desc: Jacques Peretti looks beyond the well-known budgets of schools, hospitals and foreign aid to the range of taxation projects the public know less about. Peretti finds that local councils across the UK are signing contracts with management consultancy firms who can take a percentage of any savings they find. He also reveals that hundreds of the millions of taxpayers' pounds spent on these contracts are covered by confidential deals, meaning very little detail is known about them. In this revealing insight, Peretti asks if the public deserves to know more about how those charged with managing the nation's billions are spending it.(n)

programme.title: Inside Obama's White House
programme.desc: The story of how Barack Obama resolved to reform the healthcare system in the United States, despite stern opposition from the Republicans and within his own party. The Affordable Care Act, also known as Obamacare, was finally signed into law in 2010 after years of wrangling, as senior Democrats urged Obama to be less ambitious with his plans and Tea Party protesters gained greater prominence. While the President eventually got the act passed, the consequences have been felt for the rest of his tenure, with the Republicans blocking all future major reforms after securing huge gains in the mid-term elections.(n)

programme.title: Horizon
programme.sub-title: Horizon: The Wildest Weather in the Universe.
programme.desc: Documentary following scientists conducting research into weather on other planets, using unmanned spacecraft to study the solar system and the latest telescopes to examine distant worlds. Their findings have revealed strange phenomena including rains of precious stones, supersonic winds, storms that encompass entire worlds, and temperatures so hot that the clouds are formed of lava.(n)

programme.title: Wild West: America's Great Frontier
programme.desc: The series concludes with a journey along America's West coast. The programme examines how the landscape is shaped by the Pacific Ocean as well as powerful forces beneath ground, particularly along the San Andreas Fault. The programme also visits the warm and sheltered waters of the Sea of Cortez, where animals including blue whales gather, and discovers how a small community in America's westernmost point have a unique relationship with grey whales.(n)

programme.title: Mock the Week
programme.desc: Angela Barnes, Ed Byrne, Ed Gamble, Ivo Graham and Romesh Ranganathan join host Dara O Briain and regular Hugh Dennis for the topical comedy show, looking back at the week's events through the medium of fast-thinking and improvisation.(n)

programme.title: QI XL
programme.desc: New series. Extended edition of Sandi Toksvig's first episode as host of the panel game, in which she invites Alan Davies, Cariad Lloyd, Romesh Ranganathan and Phill Jupitus to answer questions on subjects associated with the letter n. Since the questions are impossible to answer, points are awarded for being interesting rather than correct.(n)

programme.title: Downfall
programme.desc: Fact-based drama recreating the claustrophobic events in Hitler's bunker during the final days of the Second World War. As the Fuehrer struggles to deal with the collapse of the Third Reich, his most loyal followers face the dilemma of whether to flee, kill themselves or face capture. Starring Bruno Ganz, Juliane Kohler, Heino Ferch and Ulrich Matthes. In German and Russian.(n)

programme.title: Lost Kingdoms of South America
programme.desc: The series revealing the character of South America's ancient peoples concludes as Dr Jago Cooper investigates the rise and fall of Chimor, the continent's first empire. In the spectacular deserts of Peru, the archaeologist explores the vast ruins of a lost city, and learns how the inhabitants once thrived in an extreme climate. He also takes a look at the customs and rituals of the civilisation, in which people made shocking sacrifices to their gods under the watchful eye of an all-powerful monarchy.(n)

programme.title: The Incredible Human Journey
programme.desc: Dr Alice Roberts visits Asia on her quest to discover how a small band of humans came to eventually populate the globe. In Siberia, one of the most inhospitable places on Earth, she meets the Evenki nomads, a remote tribe that has much to teach the world about surviving in extreme climates. Alice also considers the claim that the Chinese do not share the same African ancestry as other peoples.(n)

programme.title: The Code
programme.desc: New series. Jesse and Ned are confronted with the daunting possibility of being extradited to the US to face criminal charges. Fortunately for the Banks brothers, Australian National Security is dealing with an explosive case they cannot crack, and Jesse might be the man they need. Australian thriller, starring Dan Spielman and Ashley Zukerman. Anthony LaPaglia joins the cast as the elusive internet baron Jan Roth.(n)

programme.title: The Code
programme.desc: After being kidnapped by Roth, Jesse and Hani disappear into the jungles of West Papua. Jesse reluctantly makes a deal with the man nobody trusts, hoping his decision will buy them enough time to find the data the authorities need. Australian thriller, starring Ashley Zukerman, Adele Perovic and Anthony LaPaglia.(n)

programme.title: Meat Loaf: In and Out of Hell
programme.desc: A profile of the rock star's life and career, reflecting on the music that propelled him to fame and charting his journey from an overweight, bullied child to his larger-than-life persona and icon status. Featuring an interview and performance by the singer, as well as backstage footage from a Las Vegas concert. The film also revisits the Dallas of Meat Loaf's early years and includes insights from high school friends who reveal where the unusual moniker really came from.(n)

programme.title: Heavy Metal Britannia
programme.desc: Documentary tracing the genre's emergence in the late 1960s, pioneered by bands including Black Sabbath and Judas Priest, who were based in the industrialised Midlands. This classic form of metal was challenged by punk in the late 1970s, before a new wave of groups such as Iron Maiden, Def Leppard and Saxon reinvigorated the style. Featuring contributions by singers Ian Gillan, Glenn Tipton, Lemmy, Bruce Dickinson and Rob Halford, guitarist Tony Iommi and keyboard player Jon Lord. Narrated by Nigel Planer.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: Simon Bates presents the edition from June 17, featuring music by Natasha, Roxy Music, Echo and the Bunnymen, Duran Duran, ABC, Bow Wow Wow, Queen, Toyah and Adam Ant.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: An edition first broadcast on July 1 1982, in which John Peel introduces performances by Natasha, Captain Sensible, Visage, Queen, Midge Ure, the Jam and Dollar. Plus, a dance routine by Zoo.(n)

programme.title: Meat Loaf: In and Out of Hell
programme.desc: A profile of the rock star's life and career, reflecting on the music that propelled him to fame and charting his journey from an overweight, bullied child to his larger-than-life persona and icon status. Featuring an interview and performance by the singer, as well as backstage footage from a Las Vegas concert. The film also revisits the Dallas of Meat Loaf's early years and includes insights from high school friends who reveal where the unusual moniker really came from.(n)

programme.title: British Art at War: Bomberg, Sickert and Nash
programme.sub-title: Paul Nash - The Ghosts of War.
programme.desc: Presenter Andrew Graham-Dixon explores how three British artists - David Bomberg, Walter Sickert and Paul Nash - responded to the cataclysm of the First World War. He begins by focusing on the work of Paul Nash, who sketched the battlefields of Flanders near Ypres on 25th May 1917. He was so fixed on his work that he tripped and fell into a trench, breaking his ribs - an accident that went on to save his life and influence his later work.(n)

programme.title: Aberfan: The Green Hollow
programme.desc: A film poem to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the Aberfan disaster, written by Owen Sheers and performed by a stellar cast of Wales' best-known acting talent. Artists including Michael Sheen, Jonathan Pryce, Sian Phillips, Eve Myles and Iwan Rheon feature, alongside contributions from the local community.(n)

programme.title: Aberfan: A Concert to Remember
programme.desc: Tim Rhys-Evans presents highlights of a special concert from Wales Millennium Centre in Cardiff to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the Aberfan tragedy. The concert features the premiere of Cantata Memoria by Sir Karl Jenkins and Mererid Hopwood performed by Bryn Terfel, Elin Manahan Thomas, Catrin Finch, David Childs, violinist Joo Yeon Sir, massed children and adult choirs, and Sinfonia Cymru.(n)

programme.title: Arena
programme.sub-title: Arena: The Roundhouse - The People's Palace.
programme.desc: The history of the London concert venue, from its opening in 1966 for the launch of a radical newspaper, to the present day. The programme explores its contribution to the worlds of rock music and alternative theatre, and how it continues to influence future generations with outreach and youth programmes offering young people a starting point for their own art.(n)

programme.title: Pink Floyd Beginnings 1967 - 1972
programme.desc: After The Dark Side of the Moon became a global smash in 1973, rock band Pink Floyd concentrated on the creative freedom of live performance, leaving the world of TV behind. Now, after painstaking research, tapes of some early historic appearances have been tracked down and compiled, offering an insight into Floyd's initial work, and providing clues as to the origins of their later material.(n)

programme.title: Live College Football
programme.desc: Action from college football as the California Golden Bears host the Oregon Ducks at Kabam Field at California Memorial Stadium in Berkeley, California.(n)

programme.title: Premier League Preview
programme.desc: A look ahead to this weekend's Premier League action, including Chelsea v Manchester United, Arsenal v Middlesbrough and Manchester City v Southampton.(n)

programme.title: Live Hyundai A-League
programme.sub-title: Live Central Coast v Brisbane Roar.
programme.desc: Central Coast Mariners host Brisbane Roar in round three of the Hyundai A-League at the Central Coast Stadium. The hosts find themselves on a 12 game winless streak.(n)

programme.title: BT Sport Reload
programme.desc: The best bits from BT Sport over the last week, including Saracens' historic victory at Toulon, Marc Marquez's title-winning race in Japan and the best plays from college football.(n)

programme.title: Premier League Match Pack
programme.desc: A preview of this weekend's top flight action, featuring key stats and insight.(n)

programme.title: Total Italian Football
programme.desc: A look ahead to this weekend's games including AC Milan v Juventus and Sampdoria v Genoa. Plus, interviews with Juve star Claudio Marchisio and Napoli striker Manolo Gabbiadini.(n)

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Magazine
programme.desc: Manchester City star Fernandinho evaluates Pep Guardiola's impact at the club and discusses his tactical and motivational skills. Plus, a round-up of the latest round of matches.(n)

programme.title: Premier League Preview

programme.title: At Any Price
programme.desc: The son of a prominent seed farmer defies his father's wishes to take over the family business by choosing to become a professional race-car driver in this earnest family drama from director Ramin Bahrani (Goodbye Solo). Former high-school quarterback Henry Whipple (Dennis Quaid) has worked hard to maintain his father's lucrative farming empire. He always dreamt of passing the family business along to his beloved oldest son Grant, though when Grant leaves the farm to explore the world, Henry places his hopes for the future on the shoulders of his youngest son Dean (Zac Efron), who would rather be racing stock cars than working the soil. Meanwhile, fellow farmer Jim Johnson (Clancy Brown) has been poaching away Henry's customers while steadily expanding his own thriving business. As Henry attempts to win back those straying clients, Dean begins to make a name for himself on the local race circuit. A talented driver despite his reckless streak, Dean soon gets a shot at the big time thanks in large part to the support of his mother Irene (Kim Dickens) and his girlfriend Cadence (Maika Monroe), the latter of whom hails from a broken home, and has settled into a comfortable place amongst the Whipple clan. When a powerful producer of genetically modified seeds receives a tip that Henry has been cleaning and reselling their product, they launch a surprise investigation into his business that threatens to shut it down. With Henry's future looking bleak as his younger lover (Heather Graham) sets her sights on Dean and the seed company expands the scope of their investigation, the desperate farmer finds that the worst is still yet to come when a tragic accident threatens to take it all away(n)

programme.title: Feel the Noise
programme.desc: A 21-year-old aspiring hip-hop star from the Bronx is forced to put his career on hold when a gang of local thugs threatens his life and he is forced to seek refuge with his estranged father in Puerto Rico in this musical drama from producer Jennifer Lopez. Rob (Omarion Grandberry) is a New York City rapper who has gotten into hot water in his hometown, and now must flee to Puerto Rico. Upon arriving at his father's home in the Caribbean commonwealth, Rob immediately forms a bond with his half-brother, Javi, who introduces his distant sibling to the seductive sounds of Reggaeton. Rob and Javi's outwardly divergent musical tastes ultimately blend to form a unique new brand of hip-hop-flavored reggae, and they soon begin to gain a loyal following that ultimately leads them both back to New York City. Yet despite Rob's growing popularity in the music industry, the gangsters back in the Bronx are still hell-bent on revenge, and willing to gun him down at the first chance they get. Is Rob's newfound status as a high-profile musical innovator enough to make him bulletproof, or could it be that he's more vulnerable than ever now that he's up on-stage for all the world to see?(n)

programme.title: Hannibal
programme.desc: Under director Ridley Scott, the most famous cannibal of cinema attacks once again. A decade after the box-office hit Silence of the Lambs, Dr. Hannibal Lecter (Anthony Hopkins) lives quietly in Europe after escaping from prison. But FBI agent Clarice Starling (this time played by Julianne Moore), who had interviewed him before his escape, cannot put him out of her mind. The reverse is also true: for a decade, Dr. Lecter never stopped thinking about her. When he is again being looked for by the police, he returns to the United States to find Starling. At the same time he is chased by one of his former patients, millionaire Mason Verger (Gary Oldman), whom he disfigured(n)

programme.title: Extreme Measures
programme.desc: Intelligent thriller about an idealistic young doctor (Hugh Grant) who uncovers a sinister world of illegal medical experiments. Dr Guy Luthan (Grant) is working through another hard shift in the emergency room when he treats a delusional, homeless patient who exhibits wildly erratic and unfamiliar symptoms. To add to the mystery, the man is naked, except for a medical bracelet on his wrist that can only have come from another hospital. Luthan is unable to save the patient, but neither can he forget the unusual circumstances surrounding the man's arrival. He resolves to look into the case further, but when he looks for the autopsy report he finds that it is missing - and so is the body. Unwilling to let the matter drop, despite strong urging from his superiors at the hospital, Luthan continues to search for answers. As this search progresses, he experiences more bad 'luck': his apartment is broken into and he is loses his job. Clearly somebody wants him to stop his investigation. Undeterred, Luthan pursues the truth, and the trail leads to internationally renowned neurologist Dr. Lawrence Myrick (Gene Hackman), acclaimed for his research into regenerating spinal tissue. Myrick's research has the potential to change the world for countless victims of spinal injury - but does this excuse the terrible price being paid by innocent victims?(n)

programme.desc: The team's mission to track the arsonist targeting US Navy facilities appears to end in success when the man in question is killed by a thermite explosion on board the USS Brewer. programme.desc: The team looks into a raid on a naval base, and Dr Cyril Taft - the surgeon who saved Gibbs' life - experiences the thrill of assisting on an investigation. programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: An American couple are attacked in Iraq, in the very same spot a group of US Special Ops snipers were ambushed six months earlier. programme.desc: The detectives investigate the murder of a wealthy state representative who was shot dead during the production of a film he was funding. programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: A Mafioso-turned-informant is murdered, and the team immediately suspects a Mob hit. programme.title: The Mentalist

programme.title: The Mentalist

programme.title: TMZ
programme.desc: This daily show-biz gossip and "expose" series was a spinoff of the popular interactive website TMZ, an acronym for the "Thirty Mile Zone" surrounding Hollywood. Created in 2005, TMZ had gained national prominence by breaking the story of Mel Gibson's anti-Semitic tirade after his arrest for drunken driving. By the time the TV version of TMZ premiered the week of September 10, 2007, the operation had once again scooped its scandal-rag competition with its coverage of O.J. Simpson's profanity-laden "invasion" of the home of a collectibles dealer who was allegedly selling Simpson memorabilia without permission. In fact, TMZ on TV had a wealth of celebrity-meltdown yarns to choose from during its shakedown week, ranging from the substance-abuse problems of Lindsay Lohan to the ill-fated "comeback" concert of Britney Spears. Harvey Levin, managing editor for both versions of TMZ, appeared on-camera as a correspondent, along with Sean Borg, Michael Hundgen, Katie Darryl and Teresa Strasser. TMZ on TV was seen primarily on local Fox or Fox-owned affiliates throughout the U.S(n)

programme.desc: A solitary drone repairman working on a war-ravaged planet Earth becomes humanity's last hope for survival in this ambitious sci-fi epic from Tron Legacy director Joseph Kosinski, and Rise of the Planet of the Apes producer Peter Chernin. In the distant future, Earth has been decimated by an intergalactic battle against an alien race known as the Scavs. The majority of mankind has been evacuated, leaving just a few solitary drone repairmen remaining on the planet's surface. Their job is simple -- stand guard over the ruins of a once-great empire by patrolling the skies, and ensuring the drones continue to function. Jack Harper (Tom Cruise) is nearing the end of his mission to extract resources essential to the survival of the human race when he witnesses a spacecraft fall from the sky. Upon investigating, Jack discovers the capsule contains a mysterious woman. When the annual Candy Industry Trade Show comes to Springfield, noted sugar enthusiast Homer Simpson (voice of Dan Castellaneta) arrives to load up on free samples, with his embarrassed wife, Marge (voice of Julie Kavner), in tow. Homer's feeble willpower is quickly stretched to the breaking point, and he swipes the rarest item at the show -- a gummy Venus de Milo, "carved by gummy artisans who work exclusively in the medium of gummy." As Ashley is getting out of the car, Homer notices the precious gummy Venus de Milo is stuck to her bottom, and he quickly peels it off; Ashley is certain Homer was making a sexual advance, and accuses him of harassment. As Ashley and a group of protesters set up camp on the Simpsons' front lawn, a tabloid TV reporter interviews Homer, and through the magic of editing makes him sound like a subnormal degenerate, so suddenly Homer is the pariah of the community. "Homer Badman" also features the voice of Dennis Franz, who stars in a quickie TV movie modeled after Homer's notoriety, "Homer S.: Portrait of an Ass-Grabber." programme.sub-title: Lord Emsworth and the Girl Friend.
programme.desc: It's the annual fete at Blandings, a day Clarence dreads because Connie always forces him to wear a top hat and stumble his way through an awkward speech. As if that weren't bad enough, he has a run-in with tyrannical head gardener McAllister, who won't let the bumbling lord pick any flowers. All seems lost - until he befriends a pair of cheeky children who encourage him to be more assertive.(n)

programme.title: Lovejoy
programme.desc: The dodgy dealer is asked to furnish a restaurant, but the items he acquires turn out to be stolen. To make matters worse, the owners turn up for the establishment's opening night. John Wells guest stars, with Ian McShane.(n)

programme.title: Lovejoy
programme.desc: The antiques dealer is asked to track down an itinerant painter who holds the key to a shameful secret. Light-hearted drama, starring Ian McShane.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: Del gets the chance to sell off a couple of antique urns - the only problem being that one of them contains the ashes of Trigger's late grandfather. Comedy, starring David Jason, Nicholas Lyndhurst, Lennard Pearce and Roger Lloyd Pack.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: Rodney aspires to be a pop star, taking on the role of the drumless drummer in Mental Mickey's band but, not surprisingly, Del-Boy manages to ruin his chances. With a guest appearance by DJ Mike Read, alongside David Jason and Nicholas Lyndhurst.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: The rundown state of the flats in Nelson Mandela House prompts Rodney to join the residents' committee, and he soon finds himself hobnobbing with council officials - a situation Del quickly exploits. Starring David Jason and Nicholas Lyndhurst.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: Del spots another sure-fire winner and decides to enter the highly profitable tourist trade - and with Rodney and Grandad backing him 100 per cent, he is sure his open-top bus tour initiative will be a massive success. Vintage comedy, starring David Jason, Nicholas Lyndhurst and Lennard Pearce.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: Del-Boy acquires three tons of lead sheeting, which turns out to be a DIY nuclear fallout shelter, so he, Rodney and Grandad collect their sleeping bags and food and have a practice run to make sure they will know what to do if the Russians attack.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: Del jumps at the opportunity to decorate the local Chinese restaurant to make a quick profit, and the results are outstanding in more ways than one. Comedy, with David Jason, Nicholas Lyndhurst and Lennard Pearce.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: Del's latest foolproof scheme to make a million involves a spot of salmon-poaching, but the wheeler-dealer finds the bracing country air is not all it's cracked up to be. David Jason and Nicholas Lyndhurst star.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: The Trotters embark on a decorating venture for Denzil. When they find a canary lying dead in its cage, they race to replace it before the deal is ruined. Comedy, with David Jason and Nicholas Lyndhurst.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: After lending assistance to a wealthy woman in distress, Del seizes a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to improve his social standing by launching his own chandelier-cleaning business. As part of the venture, he ropes a reluctant Rodney and Grandad into helping him. David Jason and Nicholas Lyndhurst star.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: A weeping statue in the local church gives Del an idea for a money-making scheme to help a hospice under threat of closure. However, his efforts are thwarted by the weather. Comedy, starring David Jason, Nicholas Lyndhurst and Buster Merryfield.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: Del-Boy enters the import trade after striking a deal with Boycie to fetch a consignment of dodgy diamonds across from Holland, and ropes in Rodney and Uncle Albert to help. Their plans are jeopardised when old foe Chief Inspector Slater picks up the Trotters' trail. Feature-length episode of the comedy, guest starring Jim Broadbent, with David Jason, Nicholas Lyndhurst and Buster Merryfield.(n)

programme.title: Bottom
programme.desc: Eddie hatches a get-rich-quick scheme that actually works - until a psychotic counterfeiter gets wind of his activities and demands a cut of the proceeds. Comedy, starring Adrian Edmondson and Rik Mayall.(n)

programme.title: Bottom
programme.desc: The grubby duo steal a car and discover the tickets for the unfortunate owner's honeymoon inside. Taking advantage of their find, they try to pass themselves off as the happy couple, but needless to say, the whole trip soon becomes a nightmare.(n)

programme.title: Bottom
programme.desc: Frustrated bachelors Richie and Eddie get their hands on a video camera following a spot of carnival-time looting, and decide to cash in by staging accidents and selling the tapes to a certain TV show. Comedy, starring Rik Mayall and Adrian Edmondson.(n)

programme.title: Bridget & Eamon
programme.desc: The TV licence inspector calls round so Bridget puts the house into lockdown. How long can they hold out with the supply of cigarettes running out? Comedy, starring Jennifer Zamparelli and Bernard O'Shea.(n)

programme.title: Bridget & Eamon
programme.desc: Bridget is a finalist in the Housewife of the Year competition and when Eamon hears there's a year's supply of free gas if she wins, he goes to extreme lengths to make sure she takes home the prize. But will it be enough to beat the reigning champion? Comedy, starring Jennifer Zamparelli and Bernard O'Shea, with Linda Martin. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Inside No 9
programme.desc: Successful West End actor Tony Warner's tour-de-force performance as Macbeth is the toast of the Duke of Cambridge Theatre, but his overbearing personality makes life hell for his fellow thespians. It would be very bad luck indeed if he was suddenly indisposed in some way - although not for Jim, his ever-hopeful understudy. Comedy, starring Reece Shearsmith, Steve Pemberton, Lyndsey Marshal and Julia Davis.(n)

programme.title: Knowing Me, Knowing You - With Alan Partridge
programme.desc: The spoof chat show host meets the finalists of the Miss Norwich beauty contest and interviews boxing promoter Terry Norton - before chairing a political debate that gets hijacked by a group of trouble-makers. With Steve Coogan.(n)

programme.title: Knowing Me, Knowing You - With Alan Partridge
programme.desc: The spoof chat show host interviews pre-pubescent Hollywood big shots Scott and Dean, the lesbian presenters from Off the Straight and Narrow and acerbic restaurant critic Forbes McAllister - who's keen to show off his new duelling pistols.(n)

programme.title: Bellamy's People
programme.desc: Presenter Gary Bellamy (Rhys Thomas) investigates the more unusual beliefs in modern Britain. He visits a `garden' cult set up by a man in Wales who makes strange demands of his female followers and talks to his girlfriend's favourite spiritual healer. He also tries to get to grips with Islam by visiting a group of Muslim clerics at their Bradford mosque.(n)

programme.title: The Thick of It
programme.desc: Nicola boards a train to Bradford for a party event, accompanied by a TV news crew, and Malcolm tries to take advantage of the situation by escalating his plan to remove her as leader of the opposition. However, co-conspirator Olly is stuck in hospital - and persuading Ben Swain to join the bloodless coup proves infuriatingly tricky. Guest starring Miles Jupp (Rev).(n)

programme.title: Time Trumpet with Armando Iannucci
programme.desc: The panel members focus their attentions on the key events from 2005-2009, including Jamie Oliver's decision to clone his own flesh and sell it as meat that instructs consumers how to cook it. Plus, interviews with older versions of Alistair Campbell, David Beckham and Tim Henman.(n)

programme.title: Rex the Runt
programme.desc: Bad Bob joins the Slippers, a gang of delinquent youths who drive everywhere in reverse.(n)

programme.title: Blandings
programme.desc: Clarence is forced to wear his Sunday best for a visit by the sophisticated Lady Daphne and her spoilt brat Huxley, but when the wealthy widow flirts with the befuddled lord and even takes an interest in his pig, Beach and Connie become suspicious of her motives. Meanwhile, after having his fingers burnt too many times, Freddie has sworn off women entirely. But then he meets the glorious Monica, who works in his father's pigsty. Jessica Hynes (Twenty Twelve, Spaced) guest stars in the PG Wodehouse comedy, with Timothy Spall, Jennifer Saunders and Jack Farthing.(n)

programme.title: Lovejoy
programme.desc: An ageing film star decides to sell some antiques, much to the delight of Tinker, who is a big fan - but her house is robbed just before the auction. Ian McShane stars.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Twelve contestants battle it out to be named best amateur baker of 2014, beginning by tackling a Swiss roll, a cherry cake and miniature British classics. Mel Giedroyc and Sue Perkins present and judges Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood cast a critical eye over the contenders' efforts.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Having shown they have what it takes to bake a cake or two, the 11 remaining contestants turn their attention to biscuits. First up they create their signature savoury crackers for cheese, and are encouraged to push the flavour. In the technical challenge, they have to prepare Mary Berry's Florentines, with their chewy caramel sauce and brandy-snap texture, before ending with a showstopper like no other - three-dimensional scenes made entirely from biscuits. For one hopeful, there will be the pride of being crowned Star Baker, while another will be sent home - well aware that that's just the way the cookie crumbles. Hosted by Mel Giedroyc and Sue Perkins.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: The 10 remaining contestants face three tasks designed to test their bread-making skills, beginning by creating 12 perfect rye bread rolls shaped in any way they like and using as much flour as they dare. For the technical challenge they have to prepare Italian ciabatta using Paul's recipe, before ending with show-stopping centrepiece loaves that will have to make an impact on the table as well as on the judges. Paul Hollywood and Mary Berry then decide which of the contenders will be the week's star baker - and which of them is going home. Mel Giedroyc and Sue Perkins present.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Judges Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood assess the remaining contestants' dessert-making skills, beginning with a signature challenge of a sponge containing a gooey sauce filling or a saucy surprise at the bottom. The technical round involves creating a tiramisu cake, before the contenders have to prepare a baked Alaska for the showstopper. Plus, presenter Sue Perkins explores the origins of Paignton pudding, a heavyweight version of which caused a riot in the Devon town in 1859.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: After last week's baked Alaska scandal - which led to Iain hanging up his apron and has since also seen Diana leave the show - judges Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood assess the remaining contestants' pastry skills. They begin with a signature challenge of a sweet custard tart of their own invention, ranging from rhubarb and custard to tropical Manchester tart. The technical round involves recreating Paul's recipe for mini pear pies, followed by their showpiece bake - a towering collection of three-tiered pies in just four hours. Along the way, Mel Giedroyc investigates the history of an ancient wedding centrepiece known as Bride Pie.(n)

programme.desc: Michel Gondry's film is a fascinating melange of romance, fantasy and illusion, co-scripted with Charlie Kaufman. Nolan Walsh (Bruce Greenwood) is a farmer who once earned his living training racehorses before his wife was killed in an accident while riding, which led him to leave the racing game. Nolan tends to his farm and looks after his daughter Channing (Hayden Panettiere) and a large flock of animals, who speak to one another but not to humans. After a traveling circus passes through town, a zebra pony is left behind; Nolan takes in the animal, intending to return it to the circus, but at Channing's insistence they keep the zebra, naming him Stripes (voiced by Frankie Muniz). Channing loves Stripes, and the zebra is welcomed by the other critters on the farm, including grumpy Shetland pony Tucker (voiced by Dustin Hoffman), slow-moving hound dog Lightning (voiced by Snoop Dogg), a New Jersey-born pelican named Goose (voiced by Joe Pantoliano), skinny-brained rooster Reggie (voiced by Jeff Foxworthy), and deep-thinking goat Franny (voiced by Whoopi Goldberg). Channing discovers that Stripes can outrun nearly any horse around, and Woodzie (M. Emmett Walsh), a local character who has spent years handicapping the ponies, is convinced the zebra would be shoo-in in the Kentucky Open, a prestigious race held at the estate of champion horse breeder Clara Dalrymple (Wendie Malick). Channing believes Stripes can win, but he'll need the help of Nolan, who isn't so sure he's ready to start training again; meanwhile, Stripes gets plenty of advice from the other farm animals about his big step onto the race track. Mandy Moore, David Spade, and Steve Harvey also contribute their voice talents to the picture(n)

programme.desc: A single woman who has served as a bridesmaid a shocking 27 times wrestles with the prospect of supporting her sister at the altar on number 28, despite having fallen helplessly in love with her smitten sibling's handsome husband-to-be. Jane (Katherine Heigl) has the kind of altruistic traits that everyone looks for in a friend, yet lately the perennial bridesmaid has begun to feel as if something is missing in her life. One night, local newspaper reporter Kevin (James Marsden) spots the devoted bridal attendant racing between receptions in Manhattan and Brooklyn, and quickly surmises that her quirky tale may be just the story to get him off the bridal beat and into the big time. Immediately suspicious of the cynical reporter's motivations, Jane butts heads with Kevin just as her younger sister Tess (Malin Akerman) shows up in town. While Jane has always put the needs of friends and family before her own wants and desires, she's suddenly prompted to reevaluate her priorities when her boss -- with whom she is secretly in love -- falls for her younger sister Tess. When Tess and Jane's boss George (Edward Burns) make plans to marry, the smitten younger sibling mistakenly assumes that her lovelorn older sibling will be happy to take part in the wedding. For as far back as Jane can remember, she has sacrificed her own happiness for the sake of those she holds dearest, but now that her heart has been broken, she's finally found the courage to be honest with herself. Now, as Jane finally comes to terms with her true feelings, her life begins to change in ways she never expected. Nolan Walsh (Bruce Greenwood) is a farmer who once earned his living training racehorses before his wife was killed in an accident while riding, which led him to leave the racing game. Nolan tends to his farm and looks after his daughter Channing (Hayden Panettiere) and a large flock of animals, who speak to one another but not to humans. After a traveling circus passes through town, a zebra pony is left behind; Nolan takes in the animal, intending to return it to the circus, but at Channing's insistence they keep the zebra, naming him Stripes (voiced by Frankie Muniz). Channing loves Stripes, and the zebra is welcomed by the other critters on the farm, including grumpy Shetland pony Tucker (voiced by Dustin Hoffman), slow-moving hound dog Lightning (voiced by Snoop Dogg), a New Jersey-born pelican named Goose (voiced by Joe Pantoliano), skinny-brained rooster Reggie (voiced by Jeff Foxworthy), and deep-thinking goat Franny (voiced by Whoopi Goldberg). Channing discovers that Stripes can outrun nearly any horse around, and Woodzie (M. Emmett Walsh), a local character who has spent years handicapping the ponies, is convinced the zebra would be shoo-in in the Kentucky Open, a prestigious race held at the estate of champion horse breeder Clara Dalrymple (Wendie Malick). Channing believes Stripes can win, but he'll need the help of Nolan, who isn't so sure he's ready to start training again; meanwhile, Stripes gets plenty of advice from the other farm animals about his big step onto the race track. Mandy Moore, David Spade, and Steve Harvey also contribute their voice talents to the picture(n)

programme.title: Fatal Obsession
programme.desc: Hong Kong filmmaker Raymond Lee directed this peculiar horror entry, which vacillates from surreal ghost story to possession thriller to necrophilic slasher with the seeming randomness of a mid-'80s Lamberto Bava movie. Yvonne Yung stars as Violet, the lead dancer in a traveling avant-garde performance troupe. Overworked and sensitive, Violet begins to suffer from stress-related hallucinations. One night, she is driving around with some friends when she loses control of her car by an abandoned cemetery and wanders off. Later, it is revealed that Violet inadvertently disturbed the spirit of Yumada, an ancient Japanese warlord who had raped her grandmother. Her friends are baffled, but the confused Violet is found and taken to the hospital. After she is discharged, she returns to work, although her director -- this film's obligatory occult believer -- is convinced that she has become possessed. He's right, and it isn't too long until the afflicted dancer is running around in full Japanese military regalia hacking up her friends with a sword. Vincent Wan co-stars with Lily Chung, Elvis Tsui, and Cheung Kwok-keung(n)
